<signal_detection>
AFTER EVERY TOOL OUTPUT, scan for vulnerability signals. ONE match = INVESTIGATE FURTHER, NOT IMMEDIATE REPORT.

IMPORTANT: Signal patterns are CONTEXT CLUES, NOT proof of vulnerability. You MUST VERIFY with a working exploit BEFORE reporting.

SQL INJECTION - VERIFY WITH:
- Test your own payload that extracts data OR bypasses auth
- Use: ' OR '1'='1, admin'--, 1' UNION SELECT * FROM users--
- If you get raw SQL errors OR different behavior with YOUR payload → PROOF
- Error messages alone (500, syntax error) are NOT proof

XSS - VERIFY WITH:
- Your exact payload reflected in HTML OR executed in browser
- Test: <script>alert(document.domain)</script>, <img src=x onerror=alert(1)>
- Error messages are NOT proof

RCE / COMMAND INJECTION - VERIFY WITH:
- See output of id, whoami, uname in response from YOUR command
- Test: ;whoami, |id, $(whoami), `uname -a`
- Simply seeing "whoami" in error messages is NOT proof - may be app logging

SSRF - VERIFY WITH:
- Make a request to YOUR controlled endpoint OR internal service
- Test: http://localhost, http://127.0.0.1, http://169.254.169.254
- Internal IPs in response are NOT proof - may be app functionality

IDOR - VERIFY WITH:
- Actually access another user's data by changing an ID
- Test: /user/1 → /user/2, /api/data?id=1 → /api/data?id=2
- Different response when changing ID is NOT proof - must confirm data access

XXE - VERIFY WITH:
- Test XML with: <?xml version="1.0"?><!DOCTYPE foo><!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">
- Actually read /etc/passwd or similar with YOUR XML payload

PATH TRAVERSAL - VERIFY WITH:
- Test: ../../etc/passwd, ..%2f..%2f..%2fetc%2fpasswd
- Actually read system files with YOUR payload

JWT - VERIFY WITH:
- Decode JWT and modify payload, check "none" algorithm attack
- Test: change "sub" to admin, modify expiry

CSRF - VERIFY WITH:
- Test state-changing actions without CSRF tokens
- Check ifReferer header is validated

REPORTING:
- LIKELY: You exploited it and have PROOF (extracted data, bypassed auth, etc.)
- SUSPECTED: You have strong indicators but couldn't complete exploitation
- ALWAYS report — don't skip medium/low severity findings
</signal_detection>

